text: Calhoun County is a county in South Carolina. The population was 14,119 at the 2020 census. It is the third least populated county in South Carolina. The county seat is St. Matthews. Calhoun County is part of the Columbia, SC Metropolitan Statistical Area. == References == Category:South Carolina counties Category:1908 establishments in the United States Category:20th- century establishments in South Carolina
